AÂ Truck has crushed two undergraduates of University of Nigeria, Nsukka to death in Ikere-Ekiti, headquarters of Ikere Local Government Area of Ekiti State. The two undergraduates, Ojo Hezekiah Abidemi, 25, and Ojo Ayomide, 21, were degree students of College of Education, Ikere Ekiti, affiliated to UNN. They were riding on a motorcycle when the incident occurred on Sunday evening, The Nation gathered. Police spokesman Sunday Abutu confirmed the incident, adding that the truck driver had been arrested.